Sentencas: Herein praseodymium-deficient Pr1.90_.Ce0.1CuO4 oxides are evaluated as potential oxygen electrodes for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Advanced electrocatalytic activity of praseodymium-deficient copper-based oxygen electrodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Introducing Pr-deficiency promotes the oxygen vacancy concentration, further improving electrocatalytic activity of the Pr1.90_.Ce0.1CuO4 electrodes towards oxygen reduction reaction (ORR).
Titulo: Advanced electrocatalytic activity of praseodymium-deficient copper-based oxygen electrodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The Pr1.75Ce0..1CuO4 (P1.75CC) component exhibits outstanding electrode performance, as supported by a polarization resistance as low as 0.025 U cm2 and high peak power density of the single cell (1.11 W cm_2) at 700 & DEG;C.
Titulo: Advanced electrocatalytic activity of praseodymium-deficient copper-based oxygen electrodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In addition, the rate-limiting steps for ORR kinetics are determined to be the charge transfer reaction and oxygen adsorption/diffusion process on the electrode surface.
Titulo: Advanced electrocatalytic activity of praseodymium-deficient copper-based oxygen electrodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This work highlights an effective way for developing the cathode candidates with high electrocatalytic activity and superior stability.& COPY; 2023 Hydrogen Energy Publications LLC.
